[sp [speaker}LEAR{speaker]}
[line [n}4.7.68{]}Pray do not mock:{line] 
[line [n}4.7.69{]}I am a very foolish fond old man,{line] 
[line [n}4.7.70{]}Fourscore and upward, not an hour more nor less,{line] 
[line [n}4.7.71{]}And to deal plainly,{line] 
[line [n}4.7.72{]}I fear I am not in my perfect mind.{line] 
[line [n}4.7.73{]}Methinks I should know you and know this man,{line] 
[line [n}4.7.74{]}Yet I am doubtful, for I am mainly ignorant{line] 
[line [n}4.7.75{]}What place this is, and all the skill I have{line] 
[line [n}4.7.76{]}Remembers not these garments; nor I know not{line] 
[line [n}4.7.77{]}Where I did lodge last night. Do not laugh at me,{line] 
[line [n}4.7.78{]}For, as I am a man, I think this lady{line] 
